---
description: Error handling, structured logging, and observability standards
globs:
  - "**/*.go"
alwaysApply: true
---

## Errors
- Return rich, contextual errors.
- Wrap errors with fmt.Errorf(... %w ...) when preserving causal chains matters.
- Use errors.Is and errors.As for matching and inspection.
- Do not compare wrapped errors with == except for known direct sentinel cases.
- Do not log and return the same error at multiple layers unless each log adds distinct operational value.

## Error boundaries
- Convert internal errors to stable transport errors only at boundaries.
- Never leak secrets, SQL, tokens, credentials, or stack internals in user-facing errors.
- Distinguish validation, not-found, conflict, authorization, and internal failures clearly.

## Logging
- Prefer structured logging.
- Default to log/slog unless the repository already has a strong logging standard.
- Use stable key names.
- Include request IDs, trace IDs, and other useful correlation fields where available.
- Never log secrets, access tokens, raw credentials, session IDs, or unnecessary personal data.

## Observability
- Instrument critical request paths, external calls, and queue or background work.
- Prefer OpenTelemetry for traces and metrics.
- Be conservative with OpenTelemetry logs unless the platform explicitly standardizes on them.
- Record useful telemetry for failures, latency, retries, and saturation-sensitive operations.